body.div:
For the DITA Map PDF - based on DITA & CSS (WYSIWYG)
        transformation type, to change the default icons for notes that do not have a
          type attribute, add the following rule to your customization CSS
      :*[class ~= "topic/note"]:before {
    content: url('../../img/note.svg) " Note: ";
}For
      a note with a type attribute set to attention,
      add:
*[class ~= "topic/note"][type = "attention"]:before {
    content: url('../../img/important.svg) " Attention: ";
}

For the DITA Map PDF - based on HTML5 & CSS transformation
        type, to change the default icons for notes that do not have a type
        attribute, add the following rule to your customization CSS
      :
div.note > span.note__title{
    background-image:url("../img/note.svg") !important;
}
For
      a note with a type attribute set to warning, caution, or
        trouble, add the following corresponding CSS
      rule:
div.warning > span.note__title{
    background-image:url("../img/warning.svg") !important;
}
div.caution > span.note__title{
    background-image:url("../img/caution.svg") !important;
}
div.trouble > span.note__title{
    background-image:url("../img/troubleshooting.svg") !important;
}
